comments.body:
[~hspencer] When I tried to use the examples you gave, I got an error on a wait condition handle.  You don't see an error about unsupported volume attachments because it doesn't get that far.  The items you show above are on the 'rollback' part of the update process.  They need to succeed.  It would be good to show the entire set of stack events.  Here is a simpler template you can use to see the "unsupported" error.
{code}
{
    "Parameters": {
        "ImageId": {
            "Description":"Ubuntu Image Id",
            "Type":"String",
            "NoEcho":"False"
        }
     },

    "Resources" : {

        "Volume1" : {
            "Type": "AWS::EC2::Volume",
            "Properties" : {
                "Size": "2",
                "AvailabilityZone" : { "Fn::GetAtt" : [ "Instance", "AvailabilityZone" ] }
            }
        },

        "MountPoint" : {
            "Type" : "AWS::EC2::VolumeAttachment",
            "DependsOn" : "Instance",
            "Properties" : {
                "InstanceId" : { "Ref" : "Instance" },
                "VolumeId"  : { "Ref" : "Volume1" },
                "Device" : "/dev/sde"
            }
        },

        "Instance": {
            "Type": "AWS::EC2::Instance",
                "Properties": {
                    "ImageId" : { "Ref":"ImageId" }
            }
        }
    }

}
{code}

Change values for image id.
